deck: Australias first international man of action
description:
Origin

Jim Devil Doone an urbane man of action with a glib tongue, a knowing look and a pencil-thin moustache was a former Australian army officer who, with his offsider (friend, partner, sidekick) Desert Head became a soldier of fortune ready to go anywhere in the world and do anything as long as it led to fame, fortune and adventure.

Creators

Devil Doone was a long running Australian comic strip that appeared not in a newspaper or in a comic book but in Man Junior, a digest companion to Man Magazine, a mild forerunner to Playboy.

Created by writer Ron Carson Gold and artist June Mendoza in 1945 Devil Doones adventures became so popular that by 1946 he was given a half size comic book that reprinted his adventures in Man Junior and then new full size comic starting in 1946, with art by Australian artist Hart Amos who stayed with the character until 1971.
name: Devil Doone

name: Lilith

deck: Demon who was trapped inside the body of Zoe Mann for 47 years. He was ordered by Lilith to destroy the town of Manson and its citizens.
description:
Origin

In the 18th century, the citizens of Manson burned several people, thinking them to be witches, alive on top of a nearby hill. One of those witches, Lilith, swore revenge and somehow made a pact with the demon Malus. In 1965, Malus entered the body of the 10-year old girl Zoe Mann, a descendant of the witch-burning people of Manson. His task is the destruction of Manson, but secretly he has set events in motion which will destroy humankind.

After Zoe Mann had killed herself (but was ressurrected by Lilith), he jumped to Jet and later a priest. He claims that, now Zoe Mann is free of him, he will father her the anti-christ when she's a few years older.
name: Malus

deck: Life partner of Johnny Woodall, who is the aunt of Rachel Beck.
description:
Origin

Being catholic, Carol took the signs of the dead rising (Rachel Beck and Jet) as the sign of the end times. She poisoned her food, from which she and her partner Johnny Woodall died. Rachel and Jet merely passed out.
name: Carol

deck: Foster sister of Zoe Mann. She was one of the original witches of Manson.
description:
Origin

Born in the 18th century, Mary Scott Johannson was 17 when she was hung as a witch by the citizens of Manson. Five generations later, her spirit inhabits the body of Lindy Ball.

Living with her parents and foster sister Zoe Mann, Lindy is a typical teenager, hanging out with her boy friend and coming home late. After a short argument with Zoe late at night, Zoe killed her. Bringing her to the woods, Zoe buried Lindy in a shallow grave. But Lindy came back to life and allied herself with the witch Lilith, who seeks revenge on the citizens of Manson for trying to burn her as a witch.
name: Lindy Ball

Maelstrom

Daniel, along with Dr. Stephen Shin, is invited to Atlantis to help Arthur figure out why Atlantis is having underwater earthquakes. They soon discover that Atlantis doesn't recognize Arthur as its true king because Atlanna, Arthurs mother isn't dead. Daniel and Shin, work on a solution while Arthur and Mera try to track Atlanna down. They travels lead Daniel to Gorilla City and to the Maelstrom.

While in the Maelstrom, Daniel is attacked by a Fire Troll who breaks his back. He then dies in Arthur's arms, but he dies happy because he saw Atlantis.

deck: Celeana is the leader of the surviving Giant-Born, old enemies of  the Greek gods and Atlantis.
description:
Origin

She is the leader of the surviving Giant-Born, old monsters of myth that fought against the Greek gods in the Gigantomahy and the armies of Atlantis.

Creation

Celeana was created by Jeff Parker and Paul Pelletier. His first appearance was in Aquaman #29 (May 2014).

Major Story Arcs

Aquaman: Olympian

The Giant-Born were imprisoned in another dimension by the King of Atlantis and the Greek hero Hercules, but Hercules was also sealed with them in the effort.

Centuries later they were freed alongside Hercules when Daniel Evans, an archaeologist, stole (or "borrowed" according to him) the Trident of Aquaman and used it to open a portal he thought would lead to Atlantis. It was revealed that he was manipulated by Celeana and the giant-born into misreading what the portal would actually do.

After they were freed Aquaman arrived at the scene and managed to beat most of them and after a long fight seal an enraged and manipulated Hercules to a labyrinth dimension with a promise to try to help him in the future.

However some of the gian-born escaped and hid in a remote castle in France, under the pretense of making a film (which explained their bizarre image). Celeana used her powers of mind control to lure tourists for the giant-born to drain their life energy.

Later Aquaman and Wonder Woman arrived at the scene and defeated them. While they were being restrained by the Justice Leaguers they started falling apart. Dr. Evans theorized it was due to them being separated too much from their original time period.

Powers and Abilities

Celeana is a very long lived giant-born creature of myth. She is very cunning and manipulative and possesses a number of powers.

Flight

Celeana can fly due to her wings.

Giant-Born Physiology

Every giant born seems unique with different abilities. Celeana has a snake like body with wings and two arms.

Claws / Fangs

She has claws on all her fingers and knife like teeth.

Mind Control

Celeana can control and manipulate others through her voice. Similar to a siren's song. It can affect extremely powerful characters like Hercules, Aquaman and Wonder Woman.

Leadership

She is the leader of the surviving giant-born and she planned how they would get free and all the giant-born follow her orders willingly.
name: Celeana

description:
Mostly, the wolves are seen but not named... with a few exceptions. Nightrunner was Cutter's first wolf-friend, alpha of the Wolfpack that traveled across the burning waste to Sorrow's End with the WolfRiders and back with Cutter on his KinQuest.

In the initial story (Fire & Flight) Nightrunner delivers the message to Cutter that the Spirit Man and other humans have entered the forest .... with fire!

During the flashback, howl for Bearclaw (and Joyleaf), we see Cutter send Nightfall back to the tribe (with Blackfell) when he and Bearclaw go alone to hunt Madcoil.

We see Cutter's greeting with Nightrunner when the pack comes to pick up the WolfRiders for the zwoot hunt before Dewshine gets hurt by the zwoot.

When Cutter and Leetah reconcile before they answer "the call of Recognition" Nightrunner runs away with Leetah ^_^

When Cutter (and Skywise) head back across the burning waste, Nightrunner becomes a constant companion until they part....
name: Nightrunner
